{
  "stem": "10572.7",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And little by little, this whole case developed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he showed me pictures of the commanding officer who had given the orders to kill the 25 101st Airborne Division men.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we took, took depositions.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the depositions then were put in the regular legal form.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we had a man that came in-- one of our members-- CIC members who was an FBI agent in civilian life before he came in the army--",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Counterintelligence corps.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so we have this, regular deposition, with question and answer, so that ultimately this deposition could be used to sentence him as a war criminal.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that went with his file.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then there were the [INAUDIBLE] that I had in Fort Meade.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The intelligence officer was a man who was a very tough guy, big Irishman who was in the 101st Airborne Division, had been wounded, sent back, and was now the intelligence officer in the prisoner of war camp in Fort Meade, Maryland.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And one day, he called me-- no.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One day, after we took these depositions from Zilke, Zilke came to me one day and he said that some of the people in the camp had threatened him that he had turned a traitor because he was called out and called out.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I said to Captain Baker, who was the commanding officer of this little camp-- and I said, transfer him.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Transfer him to Fort Meade, so that we don't have a killing here which you have to investigate.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he had him transferred to Fort Meade.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I had no thought-- didn't think of Major Erwin, I think, was his name-- that he was in Fort Meade.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I got a call from him at headquarters one day.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
